The castigation of the body should neither be immoderate nor indiscreet in vigils, fastingS, and other external penances and labours, which usually do harm, and hinder better things, It is expedient therefore that whatever is done in this way be disclosed by each one to his Confessor, who should refer it to the Superior

Let there be some one in every House to preside over everything that relates to the good health of the body, and as well for maintaining it in the healthy as in those more especially who from age and other causes are more weakly, as in restoring it to the sick, to which person all ought immediately to refer, if they feel themselves unwell; that the convenient remedy be provided,

as charity requires. y
